Package: TexMix
Type: Package
Title: Supporting Functions and Data for Geo-Spatial Analytics Courses at UTDallas, Texas
Version: 0.5.4
Authors@R: c(person("Michael", "Tiefelsdorf", email="tiefelsdorf@utdallas.edu", role=c("aut","cre")),
             person("Yongwan", "Chun", role=c("ctb")))
Maintainer: Michael Tiefelsdorf <tiefelsdorf@utdallas.edu>
Description: A collection of functions and data - mostly from Texas - is provided. 
  These are used as teaching tools for geo-spatial data analytics courses in the 
  GISciences program at The University of Texas at Dallas. In addition, a
  vignette illustrates the identification of homogenous and spatially contiguous market areas 
  built on socio-economic, demographic and infrastructure census information. The 
  spatial resolution of the data-sets ranges from 1623 food store locations, over 
  geo-referenced areal data of 258 Texan counties, to 529 census tracts in 2018 as well 
  as 1669 block groups also in 2018 in Dallas County. Cartographic, specialized regression and 
  data handling functions as well as data visualization functions are provided.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: sp, RColorBrewer, classInt, Formula
Suggests: spatstat, smacpod, colorspace, car, effects, spdep, VIM,
    ClustGeo, knitr, rmarkdown
